It was not the typical Bernie Sanders crowd.

A dozen Iowans in their 60s, 70s and beyond, nearly all white-haired and wearing glasses, shuffled into the basement meeting room of the Estherville public library last Friday, to hear from a Sanders staffer about seniors issues. Estherville is in Emmet County, in deep-red northwestern Iowa, a county that Hillary Clinton tied for first with John Edwards in the 2008 caucus.
